<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/421> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #421" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.; Degrassi 26f., 97, 376f. See Lübker no. 14." ;
	dprr:hasID 421 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/420> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #420" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The name of Papirius' colleague is not preserved. The reading of Fast. Cap. is L. Papirius L. [- - - -]." ;
	dprr:hasID 420 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/402> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #402" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.42.2; Fast. Cap. ([- -] Mugillan(us)); Chr. 354 (Capitolino et Mugilliano); Degrassi 26f., 96, 374f." ;
	dprr:hasID 402 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/401> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #401" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Antonius is a plebeian name, as Niebuhr saw (RG 2.480), but Livy (5.12.11-12) asserts that the first plebeian Mil. Tr. c. p. was elected in 400. Cf. Mommsen, RF 1.95. Papirius was probably a son of the Consul of 443 and himself the Censor of 418, hence the filiation L. f." ;
	dprr:hasID 401 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/386> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #386" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.30.12; Diod. 12.78.1; Chr. 354 (Structo et Mugilliano); Fast. Hyd. (Achillo et Mugilano); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 96, 374f. On Papirius, see Lübker no. 14." ;
	dprr:hasID 386 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/385> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #385" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy gives Servilius the cognomen Ahala, and makes the Mil. Tr. of 418 (Axilla in Fast. Cap.) a son of Priscus, the Dictator who captured Fidenae in 435 and Labicum in 418. He is called Structus in Diod. and Chr. 354. See Münzer, RE no. 37, and Mommsen, RF 2.209f., who believe these variations to be due to annalistic interpolation and prefer to follow the Fast. Cap. See 419, note 1. Münzer (RE) notes the uncertainty whether Mugillanus is the Consul of 444 or his son. As the tradition provides no evidence of iteration Degrassi would distinguish two Consuls. It is reasonable to suppose that the Consul of 427 and the Military Tribune of 422 were the same person." ;
	dprr:hasID 385 .
